00:05:29.130 --> 00:05:31.213
SOPHIA AMORUSO: Yeah, so
we launched the Girl Boss

00:05:31.213 --> 00:05:34.990
foundation about a year ago,
and I just really wanted

00:05:34.990 --> 00:05:38.130
to do something to give back
to girls who were starting

00:05:38.130 --> 00:05:41.420
their own businesses,
and specifically

00:05:41.420 --> 00:05:44.220
creative entrepreneurs,
I think, because it

00:05:44.220 --> 00:05:47.920
was my experience
with photography that

00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:50.780
got me kind of like,
oh that was really

00:05:50.780 --> 00:05:53.890
fun about having an online
shop was the photography.

00:05:53.890 --> 00:05:55.640
And it still is today,
even though I'm not

00:05:55.640 --> 00:05:57.630
taking the pictures.

00:05:57.630 --> 00:06:03.270
So to date we've given
away $75,000 in grants

00:06:03.270 --> 00:06:07.290
to girls in like art,
music, fashion, design.

00:06:07.290 --> 00:06:10.950
One girl makes these really
beautiful silk scarves,

00:06:10.950 --> 00:06:15.500
and used the grant to like
rent some space in a showroom

00:06:15.500 --> 00:06:18.560
and to make samples
of silk pajamas using

00:06:18.560 --> 00:06:21.280
the same kind of
illustrations that she

00:06:21.280 --> 00:06:22.780
prints onto her
scarves, and they're

00:06:22.780 --> 00:06:25.010
really, really beautiful.

00:06:25.010 --> 00:06:28.760
There's another grant recipient
who publishes novellas, so

00:06:28.760 --> 00:06:30.870
short-form books.

00:06:30.870 --> 00:06:33.490
Her company is called Novella
and she's really awesome.

00:06:33.490 --> 00:06:38.150
So it's the start
to something that I

00:06:38.150 --> 00:06:41.350
think will become a bigger
way that Girl Boss can tell

00:06:41.350 --> 00:06:43.850
other people's stories
other than my own,

00:06:43.850 --> 00:06:45.600
because I think even
hearing their stories

00:06:45.600 --> 00:06:48.850
gives other people
perspective and confidence.

00:06:51.569 --> 00:06:53.610
